headline: Costco’s Earnings Beat Estimates. Why the Stock Dipped.
summary: Costco Wholesale  reported higher sales and earnings than expected for its fiscal fourth quarter, proving its worth yet again as a haven from economic volatility.  The warehouse club posted earnings of $4.28 a share, while the consensus call among analysts tracked by FactSet was for $4.24.  Shares of Costco were down 0.4% in after-hour trading Thursday, reversing gains immediately after the report’s release.

headline: Costco earnings top estimates despite tariffs
summary: Costco (COST) reported third quarter earnings of $4.28 per share compared to the Bloomberg consensus estimate of $4.24. Revenue was $63.21 billion versus an estimated $63.31 billion. Comparable sales, excluding gas and currency impacts, were up 8%. Analysts had anticipated 6.99%. headline: Costco misses sales expectations, but says it won't raise prices yet
summary: (Reuters) -Costco Wholesale missed analyst expectations for third-quarter revenue on Thursday and said it had pulled forward shipments of some goods it had planned to import this summer to lower the impact of U.S. tariffs.  The membership-only retail chain said raising prices would be a "last resort", unlike larger rival Walmart, which has said that it would have to start raising prices later this month.  Target opted not to raise prices, but slashed its annual outlook.
